Microtracker is a program for composing four-channel music in 53-tone equal temperament. The scope of the program is intentionally kept narrow in order to avoid complexity and distraction. The guideline for the user interface is directness -- no menus.

To build on Linux:
1) Install portaudio v19
2) cd plugins
   make
   cd ../microtracker
   make

To build on Windows using Cygwin:
1) Install gcc, make, ncurses-dev using Cygwin's setup.exe
2) Download the v19 trunk of portaudio and build and install it
3) Follow step 2 of the linux build instructions

To see key bindings, look at microtracker/src/editor.h.
